### List installed Kernels
$ dpkg --list | grep linux-image

### Show active Kernel
$ uname -r

### List all associated Kernel files
1. linux-tools-%
2. linux-image-%
3. linux-modules-extra-%
4. linux-modules-%
5. linux-headers-% (x2)
6. linux-hwe-tools-%

